<div class="highlights">
    <h3 class="highlights__heading">Reporting Highlights</h3>
    <ul class="highlights__list">
                    <li class="highlights__highlight"><span class="highlights__subheading">Risky Medications: </span> The FDA has given more than 20 foreign factories a special pass to continue sending drugs to the U.S. even though they were made at plants that the agency had banned.</li>
            <li class="highlights__highlight"><span class="highlights__subheading">Troubled Factories: </span> The medications came mostly from plants in India where inspectors found contaminated drugs, filthy labs and falsified records.</li>
            <li class="highlights__highlight"><span class="highlights__subheading">FDA Secrecy: </span> The agency did not proactively inform the public when drugs were exempted from import bans, and it did not routinely test the medications to ensure they were safe.</li>
            </ul>
    <p class="highlights__disclaimer">
        These highlights were written by the reporters and editors who worked on this story. <span id="survey-placeholder"></span>
    </p>
</div>

